  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3766" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>Hotel Metropole, Cork. Nov: 20, 1897. </dateline>
        <opener>Dear D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> Schuchardt, </opener>
        <p>I was very glad to get your <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">pleasant </hi>letter this morning. Yesterday I entered on my 41<hi
            rendition="#sup">st</hi> year alas! How much time I have been forced to waste! I was hoping to celebrate the day by publishing the first Basque book printed in Ireland, but have had to delay it because Oregi and <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2939">Vinson</persName> have not chosen to return the proofs sent 9 days ago as <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1253">Campion</persName> has. Do not speak to me about the madness of what you call the grammatical renaissance in Biscaya. <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1062">Azkue</persName> and Sabino are both enemies of mine. Before realising their character I committed some of my views to them in writing or by word of mouth, and some of these appear in their works without any acknowledgement of their source! and I can detect blows aimed at me in the dark by them in return. They are not of good family, but puffed up by a superficial education &amp; trying to float on the surface of spanish shallowness &amp; indifference into fame. Go to Bizcaya &amp; seek the oldest &amp; most ignorance [sic] peasants! Go to Garai near Durango &amp; hear the initial <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">H</hi> still sounded! You do not say that you got my supplement to <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.5695">
Larramendi</ref>, with etymologies worthy of an Oregi or a <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1769">León Hiriart</persName>. I have written to <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.3286">
            <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">the Athenaeum</hi>
          </ref> about the announcement it made last week that your Academy is to publish <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.5677">Leiçarraga</ref>. I will try to submit a few plain questions to you about <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.837">Basque</ref> in <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.203">Breton</ref> &amp; Irish <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.901">Gaelic</ref>.</p>
        <closer>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1402">E. S. Dodgson</persName>. </signed>
        </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
      </div>
